channel.title: Need help with Utorrent running
channel.description:
Ok im using Utorrent as a "portforword". About 26 hours ago I had a server running tryed to compile it crashed server. Then I couldn't run my runserver.bat giles. I fixed that. Now when I'm running Utorrent it isnt working properly. It supposed to say a bunch of stuff under it after you run it and it wont. And my source has no object.cfg file. It is smokedscapev2. When I click runserver it says [code]config/objects.cfg: file not found.[/code]
I might download a new source but so far this is the only source i've been able to compile with. I guess my question is why it has no object.cfg file or how do you make one.
Zoro35

item.title: Need help with Utorrent running
item.dc:creator: @I_Sora_I I Sora I
item.description:
@I_Sora_I wrote:

um.
Ok…
This happened to me before; its not really that much of a big thing.
locate the file “objects.cfg” in your server files and drag it to the side pane into the actual server folder.
should work.
if not use a backup cause thats what i did, it never worked for me lol.
don’t move your CFG around next time.
if they’re out of place leave them there, they’re probably out of place for a reason.
